39362?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer","html_url":"https://github.com/normanmaurer","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/normanmaurer/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"open_issues":0,"closed_issues":42,"state":"closed","created_at":"2017-03-10T07:11:53Z","updated_at":"2017-04-30T08:33:27Z","due_on":null,"closed_at":"2017-04-30T08:21:30Z"},"comments":2,"created_at":"2017-04-04T07:51:04Z","updated_at":"2017-04-07T00:59:07Z","closed_at":"2017-04-07T00:59:07Z","author_association":"MEMBER","type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nWe have a domain which yields the following `dig` result for an `AAAA` question:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ dig -t AAAA some.internal.domain.com\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.9.5-9+deb8u10-Debian <<>> -t AAAA some.internal.domain.com\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 4883\r\n;; flags: qr rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 0, AUTHORITY: 1, ADDITIONAL: 1\r\n\r\n;; OPT PSEUDOSECTION:\r\n; EDNS: version: 0, flags:; udp: 4096\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;some.internal.domain.com. IN\tAAAA\r\n\r\n;; AUTHORITY SECTION:\r\ndomain.com.\t600\tIN\tSOA\tdevns2.domain.com. devns1.domain.com. 1491209525 3578 600 604800 3600\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 105 msec\r\n```\r\n\r\n... and the following response for an `A` question:\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ dig -t A some.internal.domain.com\r\n\r\n; <<>> DiG 9.9.5-9+deb8u10-Debian <<>> -t A some.internal.domain.com\r\n;; global options: +cmd\r\n;; Got answer:\r\n;; ->>HEADER<<- opcode: QUERY, status: NOERROR, id: 35178\r\n;; flags: qr rd ra; QUERY: 1, ANSWER: 1, AUTHORITY: 2, ADDITIONAL: 3\r\n\r\n;; OPT PSEUDOSECTION:\r\n; EDNS: version: 0, flags:; udp: 4096\r\n;; QUESTION SECTION:\r\n;some.internal.domain.com. IN\tA\r\n\r\n;; ANSWER SECTION:\r\nsome.internal.domain.com. 600 IN A\t10.127.103.71\r\n\r\n;; AUTHORITY SECTION:\r\ndomain.com.\t172800\tIN\tNS\tdevns1.domain.com.\r\ndomain.com.\t172800\tIN\tNS\tdevns2.domain.com.\r\n\r\n;; ADDITIONAL SECTION:\r\ndevns1.domain.com.\t172800\tIN\tA\t111.222.111.222\r\ndevns2.domain.com.\t172800\tIN\tA\t222.111.222.111\r\n\r\n;; Query time: 50 msec\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen the response for the `AAAA` question is received sooner than that of the `A` question, a user will see `UnknownHostException(\"Unable to find correct name server for some.internal.domain.com\")`, even if the DNS server will respond a correct answer for the `A` question.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`DnsNameResolverContext` should not fail the resolution request until all A/AAAA responses are received and evaluated.\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n`DnsNameResolveContext` fails the promise too soon when handling a redirect.\r\n\r\n### Minimal yet complete reproducer code (or URL to code)\r\n\r\nN/A since it involves a proper DNS server setup.\r\n\r\n### Netty version\r\n\r\n4.1.9.Final\r\n\r\n### Workaround\r\n\r\nDiable IPv6 explicitly using the JVM system property.\r\n\r\n### Related commit\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/netty/netty/commit/661ff2538e48977b974a78a870fec0712452dd93","closed_by":{"login":"Scottmitch","id":7562868,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc1NjI4Njg=","avatar_url":"https: